The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks and autoencoders, to generate novel sequences of choreography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of 3D point data, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of dance artists and physicists, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), respectively.
